Description: Command-line interface for StatShed status dashboard
 StatShed CLI provides the "statshed" command for interacting with the
 StatShed status dashboard from the command line:
 .
  - submit: Report job status (success, error, progress), optionally with a log
  - stream: Submit stdin lines as debounced progress updates
  - wrap: Run a command, forward its IO, and report its progress and exit
  - health: Check overall system health
  - groups: List all groups with health summaries
  - jobs: List jobs within a specific group
  - config: View and update global timeout configuration
  - group-config: View and update group-specific settings
  - completion: Generate shell completion scripts
 .
 This package ships a single dependency-free Go binary.
